.TH man 1 "28 Jul 2023" "0.1" "simple_shell man page"

.SH NAME
.B simple_shell
- Simple shell created in C.

.SH SYNOPSIS
 hsh [options] [file]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Shell is a UNIX term for the interactivationmode user interface with an operating system. The shell is the layer of programming that understands
and executes the commands a user enters. A shell usually implies an interface with a command syntax

.B Overview

The simple shell is a command that reads lines from either a file or the terminal.

.SH PATH

It will look inside al directions in PATH env variable for executable.

.SH Return Value

Always 0 for success or means failure if another number .

.SH

.SH OPTIONS
.B simple_shell
Command options will be typed after the main command followed by a space and a
 '-' symbol.

.SH EXAMPLE

[command] [options]
$ ls -l

.SH BUGS
Single space after argument.
